	<section class="py-16 sm:py-24 xl:py-32">
		<div class="content-wrapper">
			<h3 class="text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-balance 2xl:text-7xl">Your Questions Answered</h3>
			<p class="mt-8 text-xl">Starting out with rewilding can bring up many questions. Here are answers to some common queries we hear.</p>

			<div class="mt-12 space-y-6" x-data="{ activeQuestion: null }">
				<div class="border-b border-gray-200">
					<button @click="activeQuestion = activeQuestion === 1 ? null : 1" class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-4 text-left">
						<span class="text-xl font-medium">How much does rewilding cost?</span>
						<svg class="h-6 w-6 transform transition-transform" :class="{ 'rotate-180': activeQuestion === 1 }" fill="none" viewbox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
							<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
						</svg>
					</button>
					<div x-show="activeQuestion === 1" x-collapse x-cloak class="pb-4">
						<p class="text-gray-600">Costs vary hugely depending on the scale and type of intervention. Passive rewilding (e.g., reducing grazing) can have low initial costs but might mean foregoing some income. Active restoration (e.g., large-scale tree planting or peatland work) can be expensive, but funding is often available. Explore our Funding and Support section for more information.</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="border-b border-gray-200">
					<button @click="activeQuestion = activeQuestion === 2 ? null : 2" class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-4 text-left">
						<span class="text-xl font-medium">Do I need permission to rewild my land?</span>
						<svg class="h-6 w-6 transform transition-transform" :class="{ 'rotate-180': activeQuestion === 2 }" fill="none" viewbox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
							<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
						</svg>
					</button>
					<div x-show="activeQuestion === 2" x-collapse x-cloak class="pb-4">
						<p class="text-gray-600">It depends. Some activities, like large-scale tree planting, blocking major drains, or work near watercourses or protected sites, may require permissions or licences (e.g., from NatureScot, SEPA, or the local authority). It's crucial to check regulations relevant to your specific plans. Our Getting Started section offers more guidance.</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="border-b border-gray-200">
					<button @click="activeQuestion = activeQuestion === 3 ? null : 3" class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-4 text-left">
						<span class="text-xl font-medium">How long does it take to see results?</span>
						<svg class="h-6 w-6 transform transition-transform" :class="{ 'rotate-180': activeQuestion === 3 }" fill="none" viewbox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
							<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
						</svg>
					</button>
					<div x-show="activeQuestion === 3" x-collapse x-cloak class="pb-4">
						<p class="text-gray-600">Some changes happen quickly â€“ wildflowers and insects can return to grasslands within a year or two of changed management. Other processes, like woodland regeneration, take decades or even centuries. Rewilding requires patience and a long-term perspective.</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="border-b border-gray-200">
					<button @click="activeQuestion = activeQuestion === 4 ? null : 4" class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-4 text-left">
						<span class="text-xl font-medium">Will rewilding attract unwanted species or pests?</span>
						<svg class="h-6 w-6 transform transition-transform" :class="{ 'rotate-180': activeQuestion === 4 }" fill="none" viewbox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
							<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
						</svg>
					</button>
					<div x-show="activeQuestion === 4" x-collapse x-cloak class="pb-4">
						<p class="text-gray-600">Rewilding aims to restore balanced ecosystems. While some species populations might increase, healthy ecosystems tend to be self-regulating. Concerns about specific species (e.g., deer impacting tree regeneration) often require targeted management as part of the plan.</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="border-b border-gray-200">
					<button @click="activeQuestion = activeQuestion === 5 ? null : 5" class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-4 text-left">
						<span class="text-xl font-medium">Where can I get help or advice?</span>
						<svg class="h-6 w-6 transform transition-transform" :class="{ 'rotate-180': activeQuestion === 5 }" fill="none" viewbox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
							<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
						</svg>
					</button>
					<div x-show="activeQuestion === 5" x-collapse x-cloak class="pb-4">
						<p class="text-gray-600">This website provides information and signposts to resources. For specific advice tailored to your land, you may need to consult ecological experts, land agents, or relevant organisations. Our Organisation Directory lists potential contacts.</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="border-b border-gray-200">
					<button @click="activeQuestion = activeQuestion === 6 ? null : 6" class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-4 text-left">
						<span class="text-xl font-medium">What if I change my mind?</span>
						<svg class="h-6 w-6 transform transition-transform" :class="{ 'rotate-180': activeQuestion === 6 }" fill="none" viewbox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
							<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
						</svg>
					</button>
					<div x-show="activeQuestion === 6" x-collapse x-cloak class="pb-4">
						<p class="text-gray-600">Rewilding approaches can often be adapted. However, some interventions (like large-scale woodland creation) represent significant long-term commitments. It's important to plan carefully and consider the long-term implications.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
